article.description: — Yuri Covington scored 20 points as UMass-Lowell beat Columbia 89-62 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Covington leads UMass-Lowell over Columbia 89-62
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Yuri Covington scored 20 points as UMass-Lowell beat Columbia 89-62 on Thursday night. Covington was 7-of-11 shooting, including 4 for 6 from distance, and went 2 for 3 from the line for the River Hawks (2-0). Abdoul Karim Coulibaly scored 13 points and added 13 rebounds. Ayinde Hikim shot 5 of 8 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line to finish with 13 points. Zinou Bedri finished with 17 points and eight rebounds for the Lions (0-2). Columbia also got eight points from Liam Murphy. In addition, Josh Odunowo had eight points and two blocks. NEXT UP UMass-Lowell’s next game is Saturday against Rutgers on the road, while Columbia visits Sacred Heart on Sunday. ---- The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
